article.description: — Jalen Cobb's 19 points helped Mercer defeat FGCU 70-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Cobb scores 19 as Mercer defeats FGCU 70-65
article.linkText: Cobb scores 19 as Mercer defeats FGCU 70-65
article.story: MACON, Ga. -- — Jalen Cobb's 19 points helped Mercer defeat FGCU 70-65 on Saturday. Cobb was 6 of 8 shooting (5 for 7 from 3-point range) for the Bears (4-6). Jalyn McCreary scored 13 points while going 4 of 10 and 5 of 6 from the free throw line, and added six rebounds. Jah Quinones went 5 of 8 from the field to finish with 10 points, while adding six rebounds. Keeshawn Kellman finished with 17 points, 11 rebounds and three blocks for the Eagles (3-9). FGCU also got 14 points from Zach Anderson. Franco Miller Jr. also had 11 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
